CHAT.comment: Teaching. Mother , Child and Father sit in living+room. Mother tries to teach Child to string beads on a shoelace then she teaches him to sort black and white buttons in two small boxes. Child is not very cooperative. Father interjects an occasional comment but these are not transcribed. Child's speech is mostly one-word utterances and are fairly comprehensible.

u.a: gives string and bead to Mother .
holds up string and square bead .
Starts to put button in pocket .
holds white button next to black .
